  • java.lang.Object

public class PedigreeDiseaseCompatibilityDecorator

      • isCompatibleWithXDominant

        public boolean isCompatibleWithXDominant(GenotypeList list)
                                  throws CompatibilityCheckerException
        Deprecated. 
        Check for compatibility with X dominant mode of inheritance. The code assumes that all variants that are in list are on the X chromosome. This is an API decision made such that no position information is put into GenotypeList and makes things considerably easier to use.
        Returns:
        true if the list of Genotype calls is compatible with the X dominant mode of inheritance
        Throws:
        CompatibilityCheckerException - if there are problems with list or pedigree.

      • isCompatibleWithXRecessive

        public boolean isCompatibleWithXRecessive(GenotypeList list)
                                   throws CompatibilityCheckerException
        Deprecated. 
        Check for compatibility with X recessive mode of inheritance. The code assumes that all variants that are in list are on the X chromosome. This is an API decision made such that no position information is put into GenotypeList and makes things considerably easier to use.
        Returns:
        true if the list of Genotype calls is compatible with the X recessive mode of inheritance
        Throws:
        CompatibilityCheckerException - if there are problems with list or pedigree.

      • isCompatibleWith

        public boolean isCompatibleWith(GenotypeList list,
                       ModeOfInheritance mode)
                         throws CompatibilityCheckerException
        Deprecated. 
        Convenience method for checking whether a GenotypeList is compatible with a given ModeOfInheritance and pedigree.
        Parameters:
        list - list of genotype calls to check for compatibility
        mode - mode of inheritance to use for the checking
        Returns:
        true if call is compatible with the given mode of inheritance, also true if mode is ModeOfInheritance.UNINITIALIZED
        Throws:
        CompatibilityCheckerException - if there are problems with list or pedigree.
